iddop}}\n|{{Sortname|Kurt|Mann}}\n|10\n|{{Sortname|Gareth|Widdop}}\n|133\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-2016/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 2016 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2017 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2017]]\n|[[2017 NRL season|NRL]]\n|24\n|12\n|0\n|12\n|533\n|450\n|9/16\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|[[2017 Auckland Nines|Pool Stage]]\n|{{Sortname|Jason|Nightingale}}\n|16\n|{{Sortname|Gareth|Widdop}}\n|191\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-2017/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 2017 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2018 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2018]]\n|[[2018 NRL season|NRL]]\n|24(2)\n|15(1)\n|0\n|9(1)\n|519(60)\n|472(31)\n|7/16\n|Semi Final\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|{{Sortname|Matthew|Dufty}}\n|13\n|{{Sortname|Gareth|Widdop}}\n|205\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-2018/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 2018 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2019 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2019]]\n|[[2019 NRL season|NRL]]\n|24\n|8\n|0\n|16\n|427\n|575\n|15/16\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|{{Sortname|Mikaele|Ravalawa}}\n|11\n|{{Sortname|Gareth|Widdop}}\n|64\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-2019/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 2019 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2020 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2020]]\n|[[2020 NRL season|NRL]]\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\u2014\n| style=\"background-color:#DDD\" |[[2020 NRL Nines|Runners Up]]\n|{{Sortname|Cameron|McInnes}}\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-2020/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 2020 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n\n<references />\n\n== External Links ==\n\n* [http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/teams/st-george-illawarra-dragons/seasons.html St. George Illawarra Dragons seasons \u2013 Rugby League Project]\n{{St. George Illawarra Dragons}}\n[[Category:St. George Illawarra Dragons seasons]]\n[[Category:National Rugby League lists]]\n[[Category:Australian rugby league club seasons]]\n[[Category:Sydney-sport-related lists]]\n", "text_old": "The [[St. George Illawarra Dragons]] are a [[rugby league]] club jointly based in [[Kogarah, New South Wales|Kogarah]] and [[Wollongong]], [[New South Wales]] who compete in the [[National Rugby League]]. The club was formed on 23 September 1998 by a merger of the [[St. George Dragons]] and the [[Illawarra Steelers]] and they played their first competitive match in 1999 against the [[Parramatta Eels]], losing 20\u201310.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nrl.com/news/2019/09/23/september-23-manlys-first-grand-final-dragons-merger-tuqiri-is-born/|title=September 23: Manly's first grand final, Dragons merger, Tuqiri is born|date=2019-09-22|website=National Rugby League|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-1999/round-1/parramatta-vs-st-george-illawarra/summary.html|title=NRL 1999 - Round 1 - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> The club shares home games between [[Jubilee Oval]] and [[Wollongong Showground]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dragons.com.au/news/2019/09/20/dragons-announce-2020-home-venue-structure/|title=Dragons announce 2020 home venue structure|date=2019-09-20|website=St George Illawarra Dragons|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\nThe club have competed in 22 seasons over their history, winning four trophies. These include one premiership (2010), two minor premierships (2009, 2010) and one [[World Club Challenge]] (2011). These achievements are listed below in bold. \n\n== Seasons ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+P=Games played; W=Games won; D=Games drawn; L=Games losses; PF=Points scored; PA=Points against; Pts=Points; F=Finals\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Season\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Competition\n! rowspan=\"2\" |P(F)\n! rowspan=\"2\" |W(F)\n! rowspan=\"2\" |D(F)\n! rowspan=\"2\" |L(F)\n! rowspan=\"2\" |PF(F)\n! rowspan=\"2\" |PA(F)\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Ladder position\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Finals result\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[World Club Challenge]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" |[[NRL Nines]]\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Coach\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Captain\n!Name\n!Tries\n!Name\n!Points\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Source\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" |Top Tryscorer\n! colspan=\"2\" |Top Pointscorer\n|-\n![[1999 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|1999]]\n|[[1999 NRL season|NRL]]\n|24(4)\n|15(3)\n|0\n|9(1)\n|588(104)\n|416(56)\n|6/17\n| style=\"background-color:#DDD\" |[[1999 NRL Grand Final|Runners Up]]\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|{{Sortname|David|Waite}}\n|{{Sortname|Paul|McGregor|Paul McGregor (rugby league)}}\n|{{Sortname|Nathan|Blacklock}}\n|24\n|{{Sortname|Wayne|Bartrim}}\n|162\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-1999/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 1999 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2000 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2000]]\n|[[2000 NRL season|NRL]]\n|26\n|12\n|0\n|14\n|576\n|656\n|9/14\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|{{Sortname|David|Waite}}<br>{{Sortname|Andrew|Farrar}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Sortname|Craig|Smith|Craig Smith (rugby league, born 1971)}}\n|{{Sortname|Nathan|Blacklock}}\n|25\n|{{Sortname|Nathan|Blacklock}}\n|124\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-2000/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 2000 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2001 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2001]]\n|[[2001 NRL season|NRL]]\n|26(2)\n|12(1)\n|2\n|12(1)\n|661(51)\n|573(66)\n|7/14\n|Semi Final\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Sortname|Andrew|Farrar}}\n|{{Sortname|Nathan|Blacklock}}\n|27\n|{{Sortname|Mark|Riddell}}\n|122\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-2001/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 2001 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2002 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2002]]\n|[[2002 NRL season|NRL]]\n|24(2)\n|9(1)\n|3\n|12(1)\n|632(50)\n|546(62)\n|7/15\n|Semi Final\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n| rowspan=\"5\" |{{Sortname|Trent|Barrett}}\n|{{Sortname|Lee|Hookey}}\n|18\n|{{Sortname|Mark|Riddell}}\n|129\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-2002/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 2002 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2003 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2003]]\n|[[2003 NRL season|NRL]]\n|24\n|11\n|0\n|13\n|548\n|593\n|10/15\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n| rowspan=\"6\" |{{Sortname|Nathan|Brown|Nathan Brown (rugby league, born 1973)}}\n|{{Sortname|Nathan|Blacklock}}\n|14\n|{{Sortname|Mark|Riddell}}\n|166\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/seasons/nrl-2003/st-george-illawarra-dragons/summary.html|title=NRL 2003 - St George Illawarra Dragons - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|-\n![[2004 St. George Illawarra Dragons season|2004]]\n|[[2004 NRL season|NRL]]\n|24(1)\n|14\n|0\n|10(1)\n|624(30)\n|415(31)\n|5/15\n|Qualifying Final\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|{{Sortname|Matt|Cooper|Matt Cooper (rugby