{"title_page": "1921 Los Angeles Angels season", "text_new": "{{Infobox baseball season yearly\n| name = Los Angeles Angels\n| season = 1918\n| image = \n| caption = \n| record = 108\u201380\n| league=Minor league\n| current_league1 = Pacific Coast League\n| y1=1903\n| ballpark = [[Washington Park (Los Angeles)|Washington Park]]\n| y5=1903\n| city = [[Los Angeles]] \n| y6 =1903\n| league_place = 1st\n| managers=[[Red Killefer]]\n| owners = \n}}\nThe '''1921 Los Angeles Angels season''' was the 19th season for the [[Los Angeles Angels (PCL)|Los Angeles Angels]] playing in the [[Pacific Coast League]] (PCL).  The team won the PCL pennant with a 108\u201380 record. [[Red Killefer]] was the manager and also appeared in 103 games, principally as a center fielder.\n\n[[Right fielder]] [[Sam Crawford]], at age 41, appeared in 175 games and led the team with a .318 [[Batting average (baseball)|batting average]] and a .463 [[slugging percentage]]. He was later inducted into the [[Baseball Hall of Fame]]. \n\n[[Center fielder]] [[Jigger Statz]], at age 23, compiled a .310 batting average, went on to play 18 seasons for the Angels until retiring after the 1942 season, and was later inducted into the [[Pacific Coast League Hall of Fame]]. \n\n[[First baseman]] [[Art Griggs]], at age 37, hit .294 and led the team with 69 [[extra-base hits]] and 302 [[total bases]].<ref name=BR/>\n\nThe team's pitching staff was led by [[Doc Crandall]] with 24 [[Win (baseball)|wins]], [[Vic Aldridge]] with a 2.16 [[earned run average]] (ERA), and [[Art Reinhart]] with a .750 [[winning percentage]] (15-5 [[Win\u2013loss record (pitching)|win\u2013loss record]]).<ref name=BR/>\n\n==1921 PCL standings==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Team !! W !! L !! Pct. !! GB\n|-\n| Los Angeles Angels || 108 || 80 || .574 || --\n|-\n| [[Sacramento Senators (baseball)|Sacramento Senators]] || 105 || 80 || .568 || 1.5\n|-\n| [[San Francisco Seals (baseball)|San Francisco Seals]] || 106 || 82 || .564 || 2.0\n|-\n| [[Seattle Rainiers]] || 103 || 82 || .557 || 3.5\n|-\n| [[Oakland Oaks (PCL)|Oakland Oaks]] || 101 || 85 || .543 || 6.0\n|-\n| [[Vernon Tigers]] || 96 || 90 || .516 || 11.0\n|-\n| [[Salt Lake City Bees]] || 73 || 110 || .399 || 32.5\n|-\n| [[Portland Beavers]] || 51 || 134 || .276 || 52.0\n|}\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n=== Batting ===\n''Note: Pos = Position; G = Games played; AB = At bats; H = Hits; Avg. = Batting average; HR = Home runs; SLG = Slugging percentage''\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#ddf; width:16%;\"| Pos\n!  style=\"background:#ddf; width:16%;\"| Player\n!  style=\"background:#ddf; width:9%;\"| G\n!  style=\"background:#ddf; width:9%;\"| AB\n!  style=\"background:#ddf; width:9%;\"| H\n!  style=\"background:#ddf; width:9%;\"| Avg.\n!  style=\"background:#ddf; width:9%;\"| HR\n!  style=\"background:#ddf; width:9%;\"| SLG\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| RF || [[Sam Crawford]] || 175 || 626 || 199 || .318 || 9 || .463\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| 2B || [[Bill McCabe (baseball)|Bill McCabe]] || 85 || 254 || 80 || .315 || 1 || .386\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| CF || [[Jigger Statz]] || 153 || 584 || 181 || .310 || 2 || .380\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| SS || [[Ike McAuley]] || 177 || 665 || 199 || .299 || 0 || .361\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| 1B || [[Art Griggs]] || 177 || 678 || 199 || .294 || 10 || .445\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| 3B/2B || [[Bert Niehoff]] || 179 || 646 || 189 || .293 || 11 || .432\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| LF || [[Dixie Carroll]] || 180 || 686 || 200 || .292 || 3 || .410\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| C || [[Oscar Stanage]] || 96 || 323 || 90 || .279 || 0 || .328\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| CF || [[Red Killefer]] || 103 || 349 || 95 || .272 || 1 || .341\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| 3B || Howard Lindimore || 132 || 457 || 123 || .269 || 1 || .352\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| C || Red Baldwin || 108 || 339 || 82 || .242 || 1 || .298\n|}\